=head1 DESCRIPTION

The accounting configuration includes configurable settings for Slurm
accounting. It's a property of the B<ClusterSlurmConfiguration> object.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 DefaultPurgeTimeInDays => Int

The default value for all purge settings for C<slurmdbd.conf>. For more
information, see the slurmdbd.conf documentation at SchedMD
(https://slurm.schedmd.com/slurmdbd.conf.html).

The default value for C<defaultPurgeTimeInDays> is C<-1>.

A value of C<-1> means there is no purge time and records persist as
long as the cluster exists.

C<0> isn't a valid value.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Mode => Str

The default value for C<mode> is C<STANDARD>. A value of C<STANDARD>
means Slurm accounting is enabled.



